cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on learning algorithms for few-shot classification using meta-learning. It also involves training a parameterized model for a learning algorithm on episodes representing different classification problems. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper evaluates the proposed methods on versions of the Omniglot and miniImageNet benchmarks, which are commonly used in computer vision research. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes novel extensions of Prototypical Networks to address the few-shot classification paradigm with unlabeled examples. 

It could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper involves classification tasks and the proposed methods could potentially be applied to natural language processing tasks. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper proposes an end-to-end training approach for the augmented Prototypical Networks, which involves training neural networks.
